                                                                                                 81
                                                                                                       The confidentiality of public ephemeral key-agreement keys may not be protected during transmission. However,
                                                                                                       the key-agreement protocols may be designed to detect unauthorized substitutions and modifications of the
                                                                                                       transmitted public ephemeral keys. In this case, the protocols form the data integrity mechanism.


